Sentencas: Here we present a comprehensive study of oxygen-deficient double perovskites PrBa1-xCo2O5+delta (x = 0.00, 0.05, and 0.10) to exploit their potential use as cathode materials for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells (IT-SOFCs).
Titulo: Structural and oxygen-transport studies of double perovskites PrBa1-xCo2O5+δ (x=0.00, 0.05, and 0.10) toward their application as superior oxygen reduction electrodes

Sentencas: Special attention is paid to the structure, oxygen concentration, and oxygen-ion transport properties, which are key factors related to the electrochemical performance.
Titulo: Structural and oxygen-transport studies of double perovskites PrBa1-xCo2O5+δ (x=0.00, 0.05, and 0.10) toward their application as superior oxygen reduction electrodes

Sentencas: Based on the results obtained from a series of high-resolution structural analysis techniques, such as XRD, SAED, and HR-TEM, these double perovskite oxides possess tetragonal lattice symmetry and a stable crystal structure.
Titulo: Structural and oxygen-transport studies of double perovskites PrBa1-xCo2O5+δ (x=0.00, 0.05, and 0.10) toward their application as superior oxygen reduction electrodes

Sentencas: According to the information obtained from iodometric titration, TGA, and O-2-TPD measurements, an increase in oxygen vacancy concentration in the lattice with an increasing Ba cation deficiency (x value) is demonstrated.
Titulo: Structural and oxygen-transport studies of double perovskites PrBa1-xCo2O5+δ (x=0.00, 0.05, and 0.10) toward their application as superior oxygen reduction electrodes

Sentencas: Additionally, oxygen permeation flux and electrical conductivity relaxation (ECR) measurements illustrate an improved oxygen ionic conductivity, chemical bulk diffusion coefficient (D-chem) and chemical surface exchange coefficient (K-chem) with the introduction of Ba deficiency, likely due to the increase in the concentration of oxygen vacancies.
Titulo: Structural and oxygen-transport studies of double perovskites PrBa1-xCo2O5+δ (x=0.00, 0.05, and 0.10) toward their application as superior oxygen reduction electrodes

Sentencas: Tests at 700 degrees C of the electrochemical performance based on symmetrical cells show area specific resistances (ASRs) of 0.045, 0.041, and 0.036 Omega cm(2) for PrBa1-xCo2O5+delta with x = 0.00, 0.05, and 0.10, respectively.
Titulo: Structural and oxygen-transport studies of double perovskites PrBa1-xCo2O5+δ (x=0.00, 0.05, and 0.10) toward their application as superior oxygen reduction electrodes

Sentencas: These results are extremely promising; consequently, these oxides are worthy of further study and optimization as cathode materials for IT-SOFCs.
Titulo: Structural and oxygen-transport studies of double perovskites PrBa1-xCo2O5+δ (x=0.00, 0.05, and 0.10) toward their application as superior oxygen reduction electrodes
